.SH "NAME"
i3-sensible-editor \- launches $EDITOR with fallbacks
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
i3\-sensible\-editor [arguments]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
i3\-sensible\-editor is used by i3\-nagbar(1) when you click on the edit button\&.
.sp
It tries to start one of the following (in that order):
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
$VISUAL
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
$EDITOR
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
nano
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
vim
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
vi
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
emacs
.RE
.sp
Please don\(cqt complain about the order: If the user has any preference, he will have $VISUAL or $EDITOR set\&.
